    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-hot-and-sour-king-prawn-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, top, tail, peel and finely slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into matchsticks</p><p>Chop your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong> into quarters</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>carrot matchsticks</strong> and <strong>quartered mushrooms</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-hot-and-sour-king-prawn-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>sriracha</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and<strong> rice vinegar </strong>in a bowl with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>hot & sour stir-fry sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-hot-and-sour-king-prawn-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Once the veg is beginning to soften, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> chopped ginger </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-hot-and-sour-king-prawn-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, drain your <strong>king prawns,</strong> then add them to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min further or until the prawns are cooked through</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-hot-and-sour-king-prawn-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach </strong>under<strong> cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the <strong>cooled spinach</strong> as you can, then chop it roughly</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-hot-and-sour-king-prawn-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the king prawns are cooked through, add the <strong>chopped spinach </strong>to the pan</p><p>Add the <strong>hot & sour stir-fry sauce </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until everything is warmed through and coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>Chinese-style hot & sour prawn stir-fry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-hot-and-sour-king-prawn-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Chinese-style hot & sour prawn stir-fry </strong>on top of the <strong>cauliflower rice</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
